examples.en: I accepted his offer without a moment's hesitation.
A moment's craziness had lost him his wife and his job.
Firefighters were prepared to rush out at a moment's notice.
A moment's reflection will show the stupidity of this argument.
We have to be ready to leave at a moment's notice (=very quickly).
The question brought her up short, but after a moment's hesitation, she answered it.
One moment's hesitation on my part, and the elusive butterfly was lost to me forever.
If she catches him stepping out on her, she'll divorce him without a moment's hesitation.
